summary: This is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection travel record documenting Ghislaine Maxwell's inbound flight from London Heathrow to JFK on July 20, 1998. It shows her admission to the United States using a French passport.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Documented as arriving at JFK from London on July 20, 1998, using a French passport.

events.title: Ghislaine Maxwell's arrival at JFK
events.description: Ghislaine Maxwell arrived at John F. Kennedy International Airport on a flight from London Heathrow.

locations: John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK), New York
keyFacts: Ghislaine Maxwell traveled from London to New York on July 20, 1998.
She used a French passport for entry into the United States.
The travel record was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection and is marked as 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive'.
